Part 15.
TEXAS HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES COMMISSION
Chapter 354.
MEDICAID HEALTH SERVICES
Subchapter F. PHARMACY SERVICES
The Texas Health and Human Services Commission (Commission) adopts an amendment to Subchapter F concerning Pharmacy Services.
Specifically, the Commission adopts amendments to Â§Â§354.1801, 354.1802, 354.1804, 354.1807, 354.1809, 354.1811, 354.1815, 354.1831, 354.1837, 354.1861, 354.1863, 354.1867, 354.1871, 354.1873, 354.1892, 354.1901, 354.1905, 354.1907, 354.1911, 354.1921, 354.1923, 354.1925 and 354.1927, and the repeal of Â§Â§354.1839, 354.1853, 354.1855, 354.1869, and 354.1903, without changes to the proposed text as published in the March 7, 2003, issue of the Texas Register (28 TexReg 2005) and will not be republished.
Justification for the amendments is that they revise language to reflect the transfer of the Vendor Drug Program from the Texas Department of Health to the HHSC and transfer of the rules from Title 25 to Title 1 of the Administrative Code.
They also change references to forms and delete references to obsolete committees and processes.
The repealed rules have been determined to be obsolete or their content has been incorporated into other rules.
HHSC received no comments regarding adoption of the amendments and repeals.
