Chapter 354.
MEDICAID HEALTH SERVICES
Subchapter F. PHARMACY SERVICES
The Texas Health and Human Services Commission (HHSC) adopts amendments to Â§354.1833 and Â§354.1891, without changes to the proposed text as published in the March 7, 2003, issue of the Texas Register (28 TexReg 2013).
The text of the rules will not be republished.
Justification for the amendments is that they clarify the meaning of dispensing and make processes for Vendor Drug Provider audit resolution consistent with other HHSC processes for provider resolution.
In addition, references in the rules to the Texas Department of Health have been changed to HHSC, to reflect that HHSC is the agency responsible for administration of the Vendor Drug Program.
HHSC received no comments regarding adoption of the amendments.
