Subchapter W. PHARMACY LIMITATIONS
1 TAC Â§354.3047
The Texas Health and Human Services Commission (HHSC) adopts amendments to Â§354.3047, Quantity Limitations.
Those amendments limit the reimbursable number of days supply of prescription drugs to 34 for Medicaid recipients who are allowed an unlimited number of prescriptions and require a minimum reimbursable number of days supply for most medications.
The amended section is adopted without changes to the proposed text as published in the March 7, 2003, issue of the Texas Register (28 TexReg 2013).
The text of the rule will not be republished.
The amendment is adopted in order that they will to limit waste attributable to the dispensing of unnecessarily large supplies of medications.
There will also be savings from the prevention elimination of inappropriate payment of inappropriate additional dispensing fees for small quantities of medication.
In additions, the limitation to approximately a month's supply of medication is consistent with limitations imposed by many other third party payers.
HHSC received no comments regarding adoption of the amendment.
The amendment is adopted under Texas Government Code Â§531.033 which provides the Commissioner of HHSC with broad rulemaking authority; the Human Resources Code, Â§32.021, and the Texas Government Code Â§531.021(a) which provide HHSC with the authority to administer the federal Medical assistance (Medicaid) program in Texas.
This agency hereby certifies that the adoption has been reviewed by legal counsel and found to be a valid exercise of the agency's legal authority.
Filed with the Office of the Secretary of State on May 27, 2003.
